Pathway.Name: Purinergic signaling
Pathway.Comment: Purinergic signalling is involved in several processes including neurologic, endocrine, and immune system signalling.

Label.TextLabel: Physiological downstream effects in target tissue

cAMP up due to ADORA2A
->Coronary artery vasodilatation ->Decreased dopaminergic activity in CNS ->Inhibition of central neuron excitation.
cAMP up due to ADORA1 ->Bronchoconstriction ->Afferent arteriolar constriction in Kidney -> decreased heart rate

cAMP down due to ADORA3
->Cardiac muscle relaxation ->Smooth muscle contraction ->Cardioprotective in cardiac ischemia ->Inhibition of neutrophil degranulation
P2X group ligand gated ion channels
